<express_security_guide>
<title>EXPRESS.JS SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>Express.js is the most popular Node.js web framework. Its minimalist design means security features are opt-in rather than default. Testing must focus on middleware bypass, input validation gaps, session management, prototype pollution, and common Node.js vulnerabilities.</critical>

<scope>
- Middleware bypass and ordering issues
- Input validation and sanitization
- Route parameter pollution
- Session and authentication security
- Error handling and information disclosure
- Body parser vulnerabilities
- Trust proxy misconfigurations
- Path traversal and file serving
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Identify Express version and installed middleware through fingerprinting.
2. Map routes and test middleware ordering for bypass opportunities.
3. Probe input handling for injection and type coercion vulnerabilities.
4. Test authentication and session mechanisms.
5. Examine error handling for information disclosure.
</methodology>

